OL,7,FThe Lady Chapel, within the Abbey, was
OL,8,Foriginally built for Henry VII and is
OL,9,Fthe burial place of 15 Kings and
OL,10,FQueens, including Charles II,
OL,11,FElizabeth I and Mary Queen of Scots.
OL,13,FIt is also the official chapel of the
OL,14,FOrder of the Bath.
OL,16,FThe chapel, which was described by the
OL,17,F16-century historian John Leland as a
OL,18,F"wonder of the world", is an example
OL,19,Fof late medieval architecture with a
OL,20,Ffan-vaulted ceiling and hanging carved
OL,21,Fpendants.
